docs.lead_paragraph: Except for the sudden burst of activity in the European currencies on Saturday, with consequent wider range in rates, the turnover had been small and the fluctuations limited during the forepart of the week. Saturday's business, and moderate rise, was ascribed to the evening up of commitments with the approach of the year-end.

headline.main: FOREIGN EXCHANGE RATES; WEEK ENDED DEC. 29, 1934.
